{
  "title": "Packaging Cron-Driven Tasks Using FastAPI in Python 3.12+",
  "summary": "This explainer will guide you through the process of creating and managing cron-driven tasks using FastAPI, a modern, fast (high-performance), web framework for building APIs with Python 3.12+.",
  "key_points": [
    "Understanding FastAPI's capabilities for scheduling and running cron jobs",
    "Setting up the required dependencies",
    "Creating a FastAPI application with a scheduled task",
    "Configuring the task to run via cron",
    "Testing and monitoring the scheduled task"
  ],
  "code_examples": [
    {
      "language": "python",
      "code": "```\n# fastapi_app.py\nfrom fastapi import FastAPI\nimport subprocess\n\napp = FastAPI()\n\nscheduled_task = app.on_event('cron', '0 0 * * *')\ndef task():\n    # Your task code here\n\nscheduled_task(task)\n```"
    },
    {
      "language": "shell",
      "code": "\n# crontab -e\n0 0 * * * /path/to/your/venv/bin/python3.12 /path/to/your/project/fastapi_app.py"
    }
  ],
  "version_notes": [
    "Python version: 3.12+",
    "FastAPI: >=0.70.0"
  ],
  "caveats": [
    "Ensure you have the necessary permissions to run cron jobs on your system",
    "Modify the cron job schedule as needed (e.g., minute, hour, day of month, month, and day of week)",
    "Replace '/path/to/your/venv' and '/path/to/your/project' with the appropriate paths for your project"
  ]
}
